result.execSummary:
The defendant Cody J. Alexander was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Criminal Damage to Property, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Cases 15CF310, 15CM102, 15CM302 called together at 3:20 pm [Clerk SH]
[Reserve Judge Neal Nettesheim presiding for BrIV]
Defendant Cody J. Alexander in court, in-custody, with Attorney Elizabeth F. Svehlek. ADA Monica J. Hall appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

15CF310: Court examines the Defendant as to rights, understanding & intent.  
Mr. Alexander waives his right to Preliminary Hearing; the Court accepts this waiver and binds him over for Arraignment.
State files information-Arraignment--service of Information admitted, reading waived--maximum penalties recited

Constitutional rights given; plea of "No Contest" entered on Counts #1 & #2-15CF310, Count #1-15CM302 & Count #1-15CM102; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; Court finds the plea has been entered freely, voluntarily, intelligently and accepts the plea, finds Defendant guilty, orders JOC entered.
On Motion of the State, the Court reads-in and dismisses all remaining counts in each case
ADA Hall submits victim impact statement

On Count #1-15CM102, the Court sentences Defendant to:
--serve 90 days in Jefferson County Jail, with Huber/Work-Release privileges; to commence consecutive to any other sentence in being
--0 days credit for time already served given
--Defendant is required to report for commencement and service of jail sentence with absolute sobriety and without controlled substances in system; non-compliance will result in loss of Huber privileges without further process.
--pay costs of $443 (includes DNA) + $33 subpoena fees = $476 to be entered into civil judgment

On Count #1-15CM302, the Court sentences Defendant to:
--serve 90 days in Jefferson County Jail, with Huber/Work-Release privileges; to commence consecutive to 15CM102
--0 days credit for time already served given
--Defendant is required to report for commencement and service of jail sentence with absolute sobriety and without controlled substances in system; non-compliance will result in loss of Huber privileges without further process.
--pay costs of $443 (includes DNA) + $100 domestic abuse surcharge = $543 to be entered into civil judgment

On Count #1-15CF310, the Court sentences Defendant to:
--serve 6 months in Jefferson County Jail, with Huber/Work-Release privileges; to commence consecutive to 15CM302
--0 days credit for time already served given
--Defendant is required to report for commencement and service of jail sentence with absolute sobriety and without controlled substances in system; non-compliance will result in loss of Huber privileges without further process.
--pay costs of $518 (includes DNA) to be entered into civil judgment
--To submit DNA Sample upon demand

On Count #2-15CF310, the Court sentences Defendant to:
--serve 90 days in Jefferson County Jail, with Huber/Work-Release privileges; to commence concurrent to Count #1
--0 days credit for time already served given
--Defendant is required to report for commencement and service of jail sentence with absolute sobriety and without controlled substances in system; non-compliance will result in loss of Huber privileges without further process.
--pay costs of $443 (includes DNA) to be entered into civil judgment
